text: Herbert Watkin Williams-Wynn (29 April 1822 – 22 June 1862) was a British Conservative politician. Williams-Wynn was elected MP for Montgomeryshire at a by-election in 1850—caused by the death of Charles Williams-Wynn—and held the seat until his own death in 1862. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Conservative Party (UK) MPs for Welsh constituencies Category:UK MPs 1847–1852 Category:UK MPs 1852–1857 Category:UK MPs 1857–1859 Category:UK MPs 1859–1865 Category:1822 births Category:1862 deaths
